entify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3206","uuid":"ea89c2c3-ebd3-463a-834e-910b1514a3ce","stig_uuid":"7cf3ae6a-12ed-4672-9836-3226970882bd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC164652A3737A5CEF5A747F7AD6AB1D84B146E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 11 must be configured to audit registry successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 11 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278932","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278932","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278932","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278932r1141916_rule","rule_id":"SV-278932","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000587","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5274","uuid":"d06f6ce6-9910-4f5f-b3ea-dc2db989876e","stig_uuid":"7cf3ae6a-12ed-4672-9836-3226970882bd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA1C6D990759C12ADF2ED4EA9973828F2AA73DAF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows 11 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-278933","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278933","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278933","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278933r1141919_rule","rule_id":"SV-278933","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000588","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Privilege Use >> Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5804","uuid":"98256dfc-db01-47c1-aa21-a81aa0794fff","stig_uuid":"7cf3ae6a-12ed-4672-9836-3226970882bd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A8D82F89BD8022755CC2197FC72E79B1E1E7A675\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows 11 workstation."},{"group_id_src":"V-279688","group_tree":[{"id":"V-279688","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-279688","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-279688r1153564_rule","rule_id":"SV-279688","rule_version":"WN11-00-000126","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must block consumer account user authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the following Group Policy:\nComputer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Account \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 11 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center >> Devices >> Configuration >> Create >> New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for consumer under the Settings picker. Under the Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft account category, check the box next to \"Block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\". Click the Enabled radio button, then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" is enabled.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftAccount\n\nValue Name: DisableUserAuth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the registry value is not \"1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe Copilot Rewrite functionality within Notepad and Image Generation within Paint is dependent upon the use of AI credits from a Microsoft 365 Personal or Family subscription. Organizational users must not use personal accounts to login to applications on enterprise machines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1482","uuid":"a6619e64-3917-428b-990f-0fd5463f4fea","stig_uuid":"7cf3ae6a-12ed-4672-9836-3226970882bd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BE08E32F14637C7AEF30631CCBE5744AAADB0075\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 11 systems must block consumer account user authentication.' matches the expected value on the Windows 11 workstation."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Mozilla Firefox Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Mozilla Firefox","stig_id":"MOZ_Firefox_STIG","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"6","uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","reference_identifier":"7102","size":34,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-251545","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251545","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251545","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","rule_id_src":"SV-251545r1117151_rule","rule_id":"SV-251545","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000001","rule_title":"The installed version of Firefox must be supported.","fix_text":"Upgrade the version of the browser to an approved version by obtaining software from the vendor or other trusted source.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run Firefox. Click the ellipsis button >> Help >> About Firefox, and view the version number.\n\nIf the Firefox version is not a supported version, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using versions of an application that are not supported by the vendor is not permitted. Vendors respond to security flaws with updates and patches. These updates are not available for unsupported versions, which can leave the application vulnerable to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"2830","uuid":"cea9bfbb-cce1-4a6e-89cf-d85603dbcf93","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EBA700347A23214B1F63A52123A6CF92C1CCDA4C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The installed version of Firefox must be supported.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251546","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251546","title":"SRG-APP-000560","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251546","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-APP-000560","rule_id_src":"SV-251546r961869_rule","rule_id":"SV-251546","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000002","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Minimum SSL version enabled\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: TLS 1.2   (or TLS 1.3)\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SSLVersionMin</key>\n<string>tls1.2</string>   (or <string>tls1.3</string>)\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.2\"   or (\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.3\")","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"SSLVersionMin\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"tls1.2\" or \"tls1.3\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of versions prior to TLS 1.2 are not permitted. SSL 2.0 and SSL 3.0 contain a number of security flaws. These versions must be disabled in compliance with the Network Infrastructure and Secure Remote Computing STIGs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"7711","uuid":"9011dcb0-8519-4d1d-88a1-271decb18d16","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 83277A9DB31BA04A39AAAA070056B7B4D6715D1D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251547","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251547","title":"SRG-APP-000177","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251547","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000177","rule_id_src":"SV-251547r1067550_rule","rule_id":"SV-251547","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000003","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>security.default_personal_cert</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <string>Ask Every Time</string>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"security.default_personal_cert\" with a value of \"Ask Every Time\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When a website asks for a certificate for user authentication, Firefox must be configured to have the user choose which certificate to present. Websites within DOD require user authentication for access, which increases security for DOD information. Access will be denied to the user if certificate management is not configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000187"],"reference_identifier":"3614","uuid":"d754f289-ae1a-4575-8c48-1c80d6928eb0","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BB06CFE3F2AC7D8255A992E04530E982A7F658E2\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.' is not present or not in use on this the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251548","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251548","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251548","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251548r1067552_rule","rule_id":"SV-251548","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000004","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically check for updated versions of installed search plugins.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>browser.search.update</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.search.update\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Updates must be controlled and installed from authorized and trusted servers. This setting overrides a number of other settings that may direct the application to access external URLs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8340","uuid":"f3175722-fc36-4933-8280-82fd433e5b3d","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-251549","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251549","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251549","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251549r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251549","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000005","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Extensions\nPolicy Name: Extension Update\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>ExtensionUpdate</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"ExtensionUpdate\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"ExtensionUpdate\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set this to false to disable checking for updated versions of the Extensions/Themes. Automatic updates from untrusted sites puts the enclave at risk of attack and may override security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8080","uuid":"2eda3c80-41eb-4b2d-8ba2-beb1ce51b712","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BF6138D9BE2F73C19C39AA176E3A6E67DEFE6DA0\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Firefox must be configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins.' is not present or not in use on this the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251550","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251550","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251550","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","rule_id_src":"SV-251550r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-251550","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000006","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically execute or download MIME types that are not authorized for auto-download.","fix_text":"Remove any unauthorized extensions from the auto-download list.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences\" in the browser address bar. \n\nType \"Applications\" in the Find bar in the upper-right corner. \n\nDetermine if any of the following file extensions are listed: HTA, JSE, JS, MOCHA, SHS, VBE, VBS, SCT, WSC, FDF, XFDF, LSL, LSO, LSS, IQY, RQY, DOS, BAT, PS, EPS, WCH, WCM, WB1, WB3, WCH, WCM, AD.\n\nIf the entry exists and the \"Action\" is \"Save File\" or \"Always Ask\", this is not a finding.\n \nIf an extension exists and the entry in the Action column is associated with an application that does/can execute the code, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some files can be downloaded or execute without user interaction. This setting ensures these files are not downloaded and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"3678","uuid":"674b12c7-2c35-408a-91bd-fa07775efde1","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4BF5C72FD4EBEB10C60D1EBF0FCCEE6667DA94EF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox must be configured to not automatically execute or download MIME types that are not authorized for auto-download.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251551","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251551","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251551","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251551r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251551","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000007","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Form History\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableFormHistory</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFormHistory\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableFormHistory\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To protect privacy and sensitive data, Firefox provides the ability to configure the program so that data entered into forms is not saved. This mitigates the risk of a website gleaning private information from prefilled information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6950","uuid":"3e611a15-8e43-4e7d-9b01-55d0baf8ceee","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FB0EB2FD056B77284F733C0BB460FFBF7EEE65B3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251552","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251552","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251552","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251552r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251552","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000008","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not use a password store with or without a master password.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: PasswordManager\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>PasswordManagerEnabled</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"PasswordManagerEnabled\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firefox can be set to store passwords for sites visited by the user. These individual passwords are stored in a file and can be protected by a master password. Autofill of the password can then be enabled when the site is visited. This feature could also be used to autofill the certificate PIN, which could lead to compromise of DoD information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1597","uuid":"06a099bf-083d-4b0a-aba7-e67f98f43b6a","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7CBDED6DD9D3A44786387EC0A54CFF03722351A6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to not use a password store with or without a master password.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251553","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251553","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251553","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251553r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251553","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000009","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to block pop-up windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Popups\nPolicy Name: Block pop-ups from websites\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nPolicy Name: Do not allow preferences to be changed\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nOptional:\nPolicy Name: Allowed Sites\nPolicy State: Enabled\nClick \"Show...\" and enter a list of websites to be allowlisted.\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>PopupBlocking</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Allow</key>\n    <array>\n      <string>http://example.mil</string>\n      <string>http://example.gov</string>\n    </array>\n    <key>Default</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Locked</key>\n    <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"PopupBlocking\": {\n      \"Allow\": [\"http://example.mil/\",\n                \"http://example.gov/\"],\n      \"Default\": true,\n      \"Locked\": true}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"true\", this is a finding.\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Locked\" \"true\", this is a finding.\n\n\"PopupBlocking\" \"Enabled\" may be used to specify an allowlist of sites where pop-ups are desired, this is optional.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Pop-up windows may be used to launch an attack within a new browser window with altered settings. This setting blocks pop-up windows created while the page is loading.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8605","uuid":"24207e2c-84fd-44d3-9deb-9f06a105868c","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FCD618ACC2407E1DC0997E6DD37F6AEC614B2B7A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Firefox must be configured to block pop-up windows.' is not present or not in use on this the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251554","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251554","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251554","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251554r1067554_rule","rule_id":"SV-251554","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000010","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>dom.disable_window_move_resize</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\" with a value of  \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript can make changes to the browser's appearance. This activity can help disguise an attack taking place in a minimized background window. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from moving and resizing browser windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3607","uuid":"8994e289-01ee-4590-bae3-3bda01172fb1","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CB4EB4C940C0D904294F0EAF8EB13B2AF1852547\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251555","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251555","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251555","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251555r1067556_rule","rule_id":"SV-251555","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000011","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>dom.disable_window_flip</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_flip\" with a value of \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript can raise and lower browser windows to cause improper input. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from raising and lowering browser windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1066","uuid":"67ef146a-9607-45e9-93a8-a86698bf0ac0","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DBF0D5B918DF76D1AAC076E978C927E180023DC5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251557","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251557","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251557","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251557r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251557","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000013","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable the installation of extensions.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Addons\nPolicy Name: Allow add-on installs from websites\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>InstallAddonsPermission</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"InstallAddonsPermission\": {\n      \"Default\": false\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"InstallAddonsPermission\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A browser extension is a program that has been installed into the browser to add functionality. Where a plug-in interacts only with a web page and usually a third-party external application (e.g., Flash, Adobe Reader), an extension interacts with the browser program itself. Extensions are not embedded in web pages and must be downloaded and installed in order to work. Extensions allow browsers to avoid restrictions that apply to web pages. \n\nFor example, an extension can be written to combine data from multiple domains and present it when a certain page is accessed, which can be considered cross-site scripting. If a browser is configured to allow unrestricted use of extensions, plug-ins can be loaded and installed from malicious sources and used on the browser.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5784","uuid":"ec00defb-2a8a-46fa-8206-fca53ca6d812","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AE73D7A7DB895523E9DA6E91ECC4EF56045B7E95\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to disable the installation of extensions.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251558","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251558","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251558","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251558r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251558","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000014","rule_title":"Background submission of information to Mozilla must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Telemetry\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableTelemetry</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableTelemetry\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableTelemetry\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firefox by default sends information about Firefox to Mozilla servers. There should be no background submission of technical and other information from DoD computers to Mozilla with portions posted publicly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7481","uuid":"f8b5d671-3a05-4cde-b1d9-569adde369bd","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7191B6D3F2712E76FF3B45391D0EBD2AD57C9F4B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Background submission of information to Mozilla must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251559","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251559","title":"SRG-APP-000266","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251559","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","rule_id_src":"SV-251559r961167_rule","rule_id":"SV-251559","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000015","rule_title":"Firefox development tools must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Developer Tools\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableDeveloperTools</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableDeveloperTools\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableDeveloperTools\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information needed by an attacker to begin looking for possible vulnerabilities in a web browser includes any information about the web browser and plug-ins or modules being used. When debugging or trace information is enabled in a production web browser, information about the web browser, such as web browser type, version, patches installed, plug-ins and modules installed, type of code being used by the hosted application, and any back ends being used for data storage may be displayed. Because this information may be placed in logs and general messages during normal operation of the web browser, an attacker does not have to cause an error condition to gain this information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"3877","uuid":"ac582a7a-ec36-4134-b2b1-089dadb6a4a3","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D57485288EFB8C22C4FCEDFCF6AFF746746AAC2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox development tools must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251560","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251560","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251560","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","rule_id_src":"SV-251560r1067559_rule","rule_id":"SV-251560","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000016","rule_title":"Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.","fix_text":"Install the DOD root certificates. Other AO-approved certificates may also be used. Certificates designed for SIPRNet may be used as appropriate.\n\nOn Windows, import certificates from the operating system by using Certificates >> Import Enterprise Roots (Certificates) via policy or Group Policy Object (GPO).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences#privacy\" in the browser window. \n\nScroll down to the bottom and select \"View Certificates...\".\n\nIn the Certificate Manager window, select the \"Authorities\" tab.\n\nScroll through the Certificate Name list to the U.S. Government heading. Look for the entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5.\n\nIf there are entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5, select them individually.\n\nClick \"View\".\n\nVerify the issuer name is \"US Government\".\n\nIf there are no entries for the appropriate DOD root certificates, this is a finding. If other AO-approved certificates are used, this is not a finding. If SIPRNet-specific certificates are used, this is not a finding.\n\nNote: In a Windows environment, use of policy setting \"security.enterprise_roots.enabled=true\" will point Firefox to the Windows Trusted Root Certification Authority Store. This is not a finding. It can also be set via the policy Certificates >> ImportEnterpriseRoots, which can be verified via \"about:policies\".","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The DOD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DOD Certificate Authority (CA).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"1320","uuid":"8483861c-5c2e-428b-9fa3-d64f9a324a78","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A6B94BA791D2246CA06AEBFC7CBA8F66DECEEAAE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251562","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251562","title":"SRG-APP-000326","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251562","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000326","rule_id_src":"SV-251562r1156569_rule","rule_id":"SV-251562","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000018","rule_title":"Firefox must prevent the user from quickly deleting data.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Mozilla >> Firefox.\nPolicy Name: Disable Forget Button\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableForgetButton</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableForgetButton\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Enter \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableForgetButton\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"There should not be an option for a user to \"forget\" work they have done. This is required to meet nonrepudiation controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"5013","uuid":"11350891-760b-4824-a0f9-170f304a762b","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 37615356BFCFB7E55E66D21B4452AE46D8D9EBAA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must prevent the user from quickly deleting data.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251563","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251563","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251563","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251563r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251563","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000019","rule_title":"Firefox private browsing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Private Browsing\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisablePrivateBrowsing</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePrivateBrowsing\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisablePrivateBrowsing\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Private browsing allows the user to browse the internet without recording their browsing history/activity. From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable. Best practice requires that browser history is retained.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5933","uuid":"ddf08aea-9d1d-4b50-9e17-a06e1e6fe133","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3229D8221B4AC1A73304746C175399328EBB187C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox private browsing must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251564","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251564","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251564","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251564r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251564","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000020","rule_title":"Firefox search suggestions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Search\nPolicy Name: Search Suggestions\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SearchSuggestEnabled</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SearchSuggestEnabled\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"SearchSuggestEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Search suggestions must be disabled as this could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3167","uuid":"1480734a-2ae9-4371-a888-0b20e3cfcb0e","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F2A93072A7D1F530015469CB0965D534D83EB0C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox search suggestions must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251565","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251565","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251565","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251565r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251565","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000021","rule_title":"Firefox autoplay must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Permissions\\Autoplay\nPolicy Name: Default autoplay level\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Block Audio and Video\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Permissions</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>Autoplay</key>\n  <dict>\n    <string>block-audio-video</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n \nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Permissions\": {\n  \"Autoplay\": {\n    \"Default\": \"block-audio-video\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Permissions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Autoplay\" with a value of \"Default\" and \"Block-audio-video\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Autoplay allows the user to control whether videos can play automatically (without user consent) with audio content. The user must be able to select content that is run within the browser window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3627","uuid":"1a014db4-2f8f-48a8-b4b2-9dd2310a65d1","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 38A74C7CA21BFC0765D53C1BA5FEACC0AFE82AA4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox autoplay must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251566","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251566","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251566","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251566r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251566","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000022","rule_title":"Firefox network prediction must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Network Prediction\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>NetworkPrediction</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"NetworkPrediction\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"NetworkPrediction\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If network prediction is enabled, requests to URLs are made without user consent. The browser should always make a direct DNS request without prefetching occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7283","uuid":"fd736525-998d-4e2a-b131-172eb0b6e29d","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C32FAAAE0A483EE1B62EFD8B4A2CC90529515F41\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox network prediction must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251567","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251567","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251567","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251567r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251567","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000023","rule_title":"Firefox fingerprinting protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Fingerprinting\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>EnableTrackingProtection</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Fingerprinting</key>\n <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Fingerprinting\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Fingerprinting\"  with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nFingerprinting scripts collect information about browser and device configuration, such as operating system, screen resolution, and other settings. By compiling these pieces of data, fingerprinters create a unique profile that can be used to track the user around the web.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2091","uuid":"bef7d557-4e8a-4fdd-894d-791dc1e3c935","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 901D49508F4E27E55734E8AB4107B41A108A2232\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox fingerprinting protection must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251568","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251568","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251568","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251568r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251568","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000024","rule_title":"Firefox cryptomining protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Cryptomining\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>EnableTrackingProtection</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Cryptomining</key>\n <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Cryptomining\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Cryptomining\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nCryptomining scripts use a computer's central processing unit to invisibly mine cryptocurrency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2697","uuid":"318cbb93-56d5-4d44-99d0-efe049ce8524","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7FD681CD83DA2DF0DADF23E9016D5F39558EF627\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox cryptomining protection must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251569","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251569","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251569","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251569r1067561_rule","rule_id":"SV-251569","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000025","rule_title":"Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>browser.contentblocking.category</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <string>strict</string>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.contentblocking.category\" with a value of  \"strict\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Tracking generally refers to content, cookies, or scripts that can collect browsing data across multiple sites.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of nonessential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5684","uuid":"097c3c88-fe9b-4e42-ad65-a29a6f066962","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 954F2B88042F6F134AED5A38ECB9C1EFC0D562BB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251570","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251570","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251570","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251570r1067563_rule","rule_id":"SV-251570","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000026","rule_title":"Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n\"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n\"Value\": false,\n\"Status\": \"locked\"\n},","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program makes it easier for users to discover extensions that have been reviewed for security, functionality, and user experience. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8366","uuid":"dd8f20dd-56c0-4eeb-9f8a-24a4b916fb89","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B0F846FE6C69B8DC254A637EF6E8E7FB0479C435\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251571","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251571","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251571","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251571r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251571","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000027","rule_title":"Firefox deprecated ciphers must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Disabled Ciphers\nPolicy Name: TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisabledCiphers</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA</key>\n    <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisabledCiphers\": {\n  \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"DisabledCiphers\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\" with a value of  \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A weak cipher is defined as an encryption/decryption algorithm that uses a key of insufficient length. Using an insufficient length for a key in an encryption/decryption algorithm opens up the possibility (or probability) that the encryption scheme could be broken.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4683","uuid":"0d474827-cdfc-4d1c-80a7-4f09c5bba283","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B37D6290120734615C3FF878E00EDF9CE0790BB\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Firefox deprecated ciphers must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251572","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251572","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251572","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251572r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251572","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000028","rule_title":"Firefox must not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\User Messaging\nPolicy Name: Extension Recommendations\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>UserMessaging</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>ExtensionRecommendations</key>\n  <false/>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"UserMessaging\": {\n  \"ExtensionRecommendations\": false\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"UserMessaging\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"ExtensionRecommendations\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program recommends extensions to users as they surf the web.\n\nThe user must not be encouraged to install extensions from the websites they visit. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5247","uuid":"30ac6676-af10-4fcd-927b-2a3a3bd225a1","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 62B2243082F38F656B42116490E59DD5136956C1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox must not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251573","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251573","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251573","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251573r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251573","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000029","rule_title":"The Firefox New Tab page must not show Top Sites, Sponsored Top Sites, Pocket Recommendations, Sponsored Pocket Stories, Searches, Highlights, or Snippets.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Customize Firefox Home\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Search\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Top Sites\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Top Sites\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Recommended by Pocket\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Pocket Stories\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Download History\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Snippets\"\nPolicy Value: Check \"Do not allow settings to be changed\"\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>FirefoxHome</key>\n<dict>\n<key>Search</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>TopSites</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>SponsoredTopSites</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>Pocket</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>SponsoredPocket</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>Highlights</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>Snippets</key>\n  <false/>\n<key>Locked</key>\n  <true/>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"FirefoxHome\": {\n  \"Search\": false,\n  \"TopSites\": false,\n  \"SponsoredTopSites\": false,\n  \"Pocket\": false,\n  \"SponsoredPocket\": false,\n  \"Highlights\": false,\n  \"Snippets\": false,\n  \"locked\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Search\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"TopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredTopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Pocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredPocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Highlights\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Snippets\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The New Tab page by default shows a list of built-in top sites, as well as the top sites the user has visited.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.\n\nThe new tab page must not actively show user activity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2547","uuid":"9d361a43-ed20-44f0-ab99-c77f2a5e93ef","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B77B0FE3B36DFBAC59DABF5133A0428D4F98F10\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Firefox New Tab page must not show Top Sites, Sponsored Top Sites, Pocket Recommendations, Sponsored Pocket Stories, Searches, Highlights, or Snippets.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251577","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251577","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251577","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251577r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251577","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000033","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DNS Over HTTPS\nPolicy Name: Enabled\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DNSOverHTTPS</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Enabled</key>\n    <false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DNSOverHTTPS\": {\"Enabled\": false}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DNSOverHTTPS\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"DNS over HTTPS has generally not been adopted in the DoD. DNS is tightly controlled.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include, but are not limited to, advertising software or browser plug-ins not related to requirements or providing a wide array of functionality not required for every mission, but cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4053","uuid":"ccfa64ef-d54b-4226-8ea8-e1c61326728d","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F49CE66CB0D47753D0731FA3DDE37640FE822DF7\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Firefox must be configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251578","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251578","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251578","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251578r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251578","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000034","rule_title":"Firefox accounts must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Firefox Accounts\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisableFirefoxAccounts</key>\n  <true/> \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFirefoxAccounts\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFirefoxAccounts\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disable Firefox Accounts integration (Sync). \n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6023","uuid":"c5b5154b-9ec3-4d13-a75c-fcbfe539dc0b","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F18F0848240D230BDAB41638BAFF20A550B20DA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox accounts must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251580","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251580","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251580","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251580r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251580","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000036","rule_title":"Firefox feedback reporting must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Feedback Commands\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisableFeedbackCommands</key>\n  <true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFeedbackCommands\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFeedbackCommands\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disable the menus for reporting sites (Submit Feedback, Report Deceptive Site). \n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3019","uuid":"f0d56a07-618b-448d-94af-1b8e47d7052f","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E602F1B822EF891862ED2F4A66175F014CF369B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox feedback reporting must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-251581","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251581","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251581","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-251581r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251581","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000037","rule_title":"Firefox encrypted media extensions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy Name: Enable Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Lock Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>EncryptedMediaExtensions</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Enabled</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Locked</key>\n    <true/> \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EncryptedMediaExtensions\": {\n  \"Enabled\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EncryptedMediaExtensions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" set to \"false\" or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" set to \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable or disable Encrypted Media Extensions and optionally lock it.\n\nIf \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox does not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) unless the user consents to installing them.\n\nIf \"Locked\" is set to \"true\" and \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox will not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) or ask the user to install them.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8142","uuid":"86298539-cc30-479c-8a3f-724d9f1b64bc","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0914E12CB55032B89756ABB8C577CB5278A13099\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Firefox encrypted media extensions must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-252881","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252881","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252881","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-252881r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252881","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000017","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not delete data upon shutdown.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Clear data when browser is closed\nPolicy Name: Cache, Cookies, Download History, Form & Search History, Browsing History, Active Logins, Site Preferences, Offline Website Data\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Locked\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SanitizeOnShutdown</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>Cache</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Cookies</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Downloads</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>FormData</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>History</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Sessions</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>SiteSettings</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>OfflineApps</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Locked</key>\n  <true/>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SanitizeOnShutdown\": {\n  \"Cache\": false,\n  \"Cookies\": false,\n  \"Downloads\": false,\n  \"FormData\": false,\n  \"History\": false,\n  \"Sessions\": false,\n  \"SiteSettings\": false,\n  \"OfflineApps\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true \n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"SanitizeOnShutdown\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have {\"Cache\":false,\"Cookies\":false,\"Downloads\":false,\"FormData\":false,\"Sessions\":false,\"History\":false,\"OfflineApps\":false,\"SiteSettings\":false,\"Locked\":true}, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"For diagnostic purposes, data must remain behind when the browser is closed. This is required to meet non-repudiation controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4247","uuid":"f6f9747a-eb98-4fd3-a89d-56600b0f060f","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3544C3B60CD7E6BBE8AEC56985A1528139A4E07D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox must be configured to not delete data upon shutdown.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-252908","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252908","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252908","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-252908r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252908","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000038","rule_title":"Pocket must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Pocket\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisablePocket</key>\n <true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePocket\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisablePocket\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Pocket, previously known as Read It Later, is a social bookmarking service for storing, sharing, and discovering web bookmarks. Data gathering cloud services such as this are generally disabled in the DoD.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6607","uuid":"df286cf3-4e70-452c-8321-d73affbabc66","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 686CC3B5C742380E53A21A87DB39C7BB51430188\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Pocket must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-252909","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252909","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252909","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-252909r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252909","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000039","rule_title":"Firefox Studies must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Firefox Studies\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisableFirefoxStudies</key>\n <true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFirefoxStudies\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFirefoxStudies\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Studies try out different features and ideas before they are released to all Firefox users. Testing beta software is not in the DoD user's mission.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3189","uuid":"3c49945b-dfa7-4491-b65a-7c33c6bab523","stig_uuid":"d12cf88b-d455-4178-abc9-b4dd13b124aa","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FDCF2006ED274EEBFBACF5C32DC9850F7FE1D19C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Firefox Studies must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Mozilla Firefox browser."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-23T17:12:42.0000000+00:00","module":{"name":"Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks","version":"1.2604.2"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Edge Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Edge","stig_id":"MS_Edge_STIG","release_info":"Release: 5 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","reference_identifier":"2377","size":61,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-235719","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235719","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235719","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id_src":"SV-235719r1156558_rule","rule_id":"SV-235719","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000001","rule_title":"User control of proxy settings must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Proxy server/Proxy Settings\" to \"Enabled\" and define a value for \"ProxyMode\".\n\n\"ProxyMode\" must be defined and set to one of the following: \"direct\", \"system\", \"auto_detect\", \"fixed_servers\", or \"pac_script\".\n\nConsult Microsoft documentation for proper configuration of the text string required to define the \"Proxy Settings\" value.\n\nExample:  {\"ProxyMode\": \"fixed_servers\", \"ProxyServer\": \"127.0.0.1:8080\"}\n\n\"ProxyPacUrl\", \"ProxyServer\", or \"ProxyBypassList\" are optional.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Proxy server/Proxy Settings\" must be \"Enabled\", and have a \"Proxy Settings\" value defined for \"ProxyMode\".\n\n\"ProxyMode\" must be defined and set to one of the following: \"direct\", \"system\", \"auto_detect\", \"fixed_servers\", or \"pac_script\".\n\nConsult Microsoft documentation for proper configuration of the text string required to define the \"Proxy Settings\" value.\n\nExample:  {\"ProxyMode\": \"fixed_servers\", \"ProxyServer\": \"123.123.123.123:8080\"}\n\nValues for \"ProxyPacUrl\", \"ProxyServer\", or \"ProxyBypassList\" are optional.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the REG_SZ value for \"ProxySettings\" does not have \"ProxyMode\" configured, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This action configures the proxy settings for Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, Microsoft Edge ignores all proxy-related options specified from the command line.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can choose their own proxy settings.\n\nThis policy overrides the following individual policies:\n- ProxyMode.\n- ProxyPacUrl. \n- ProxyServer. \n- ProxyBypassList.\n\nSetting the ProxySettings policy accepts the following fields:\n- ProxyMode, which allows for the proxy server used by Microsoft Edge to be specified and prevents users from changing proxy settings.\n- ProxyPacUrl, a URL to a proxy .pac file.\n- ProxyServer, a URL for the proxy server.\n- ProxyBypassList, a list of proxy hosts that Microsoft Edge bypasses.\n\nFor ProxyMode, the following values have the noted impact:\n- direct, a proxy is never used and all other fields are ignored.\n- system, the system's proxy is used and all other fields are ignored.\n- auto_detect, all other fields are ignored.\n- fixed_servers, the ProxyServer and ProxyBypassList fields are used.\n- pac_script, the ProxyPacUrl and ProxyBypassList fields are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"2467","uuid":"df32c14c-3721-4c18-842b-a3b9031ae45a","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ACE447204DAB8E449581B672CC82E80952F8ED2C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User control of proxy settings must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235720","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235720","title":"SRG-APP-000073","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235720","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","rule_id_src":"SV-235720r960852_rule","rule_id":"SV-235720","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000002","rule_title":"Bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PreventSmartScreenPromptOverride\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows a decision to be made on whether users can override the Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about potentially malicious websites.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, users cannot ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings, and are blocked from continuing to the site.\n\nIf this setting is disabled or not configured, users can ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings and continue to the site.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000870"],"reference_identifier":"9994","uuid":"20b1de83-db21-4be7-ab71-b51fc54cb2ca","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4606C4E95F74B04F6857A689515D210E3DAD16F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235721","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235721","title":"SRG-APP-000073","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235721","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","rule_id_src":"SV-235721r960852_rule","rule_id":"SV-235721","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000003","rule_title":"Bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads\" must to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PreventSmartScreenPromptOverrideForFiles\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows a decision to be made on whether users can override Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about unverified downloads.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, users cannot ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings, and are prevented from completing the unverified downloads.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or not configured, users can ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings and complete unverified downloads.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000870"],"reference_identifier":"3030","uuid":"1c2cc749-a9e5-46ec-b954-a479d90f3127","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A284EE5FB83F1764D9C03EEA5AFC713EB67E45AC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235722","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235722","title":"SRG-APP-000073","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235722","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","rule_id_src":"SV-235722r960852_rule","rule_id":"SV-235722","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000004","rule_title":"The list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings must be allowlisted if used.","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"SmartScreenAllowListDomains\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen won't trigger warnings\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nSmartScreenAllowListDomains may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenAllowListDomains\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenAllowListDomains\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configure the list of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen trusted domains. This means Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not check for potentially malicious resources, such as phishing software and other malware, if the source URLs match these domains. The Microsoft Defender SmartScreen download protection service will not check downloads hosted on these domains.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen trusts these domains. If the policy is disabled or not set, default Microsoft Defender SmartScreen protection is applied to all resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000870"],"reference_identifier":"9278","uuid":"ed314fd2-ace8-4b6f-9334-060e3af6046f","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A2E939D866B73701C0C870C9DFDF3B2FA125C3F2\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings must be allowlisted if used.' is not present or not in use on this the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235723","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235723","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235723","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","rule_id_src":"SV-235723r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-235723","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000005","rule_title":"InPrivate mode must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure InPrivate mode availability\" to \"enabled\" and select \"InPrivate mode disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure InPrivate mode availability\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"InPrivate mode disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"InPrivateModeAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting specifies whether the user can open pages in InPrivate mode in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or set it to \"Enabled\", users can open pages in InPrivate mode.\n\nSet this policy to \"Disabled\" to stop users from using InPrivate mode.\n\nSet this policy to \"Forced\" to always use InPrivate mode.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- Enabled (0) = InPrivate mode available\n- Disabled (1) = InPrivate mode disabled\n- Forced (2) = InPrivate mode forced","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"8779","uuid":"1d9441fd-2bc8-4be1-a541-8e1593f51eef","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-235724","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235724","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235724","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235724r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235724","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000006","rule_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Continue running background apps after Microsoft Edge closes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Continue running background apps after Microsoft Edge closes\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BackgroundModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Background processing allows Microsoft Edge processes to start at OS sign-in and keep running after the last browser window is closed. In this scenario, background apps and the current browsing session remain active, including any session cookies. An open background process displays an icon in the system tray, and can be closed from there.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, background mode is turned on.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, background mode is turned off.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, background mode is initially turned off, and the user can configure its behavior in edge://settings/system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7599","uuid":"768ec07b-53d8-4a27-97e0-e8b21b24f0f0","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 31B76F6EFF09CAA7704715F6A4C48211F59D5946\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Background processing must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235725","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235725","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235725","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235725r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235725","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000008","rule_title":"The ability of sites to show pop-ups must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default pop-up window setting\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to show  pop-ups\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default pop-up window setting\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to show  pop-ups\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for DefaultPopupsSetting is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set whether websites can show pop-up windows. Pop-ups can be allowed on all websites (\"AllowPopups\") or blocked on all sites (\"BlockPopups\").\n\nIf this policy is configured, pop-up windows are blocked by default, and users can change this setting.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowPopups (1) = Allow all sites to show pop-ups.\n- BlockPopups (2) = Do not allow any site to show pop-ups.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6966","uuid":"aa693b15-9297-4ec9-b38b-bf7585855742","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1A6D974E816D5E21F9D61C4E8100CCFD17F47D4F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The ability of sites to show pop-ups must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235726","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235726","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235726","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235726r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235726","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000009","rule_title":"The default search provider must be set to use an encrypted connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Manage Search Engines\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Manage Search Engines\" must be configured.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nExample REG_SZ value text for \"ManagedSearchEngines\":\n[{\"allow_search_engine_discovery\": false},{\"is_default\": true,\"name\": \"Microsoft Bing\",\"keyword\": \"bing\",\"search_url\": \"https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms}\"},{\"name\": \"Google\",\"keyword\": \"google\",\"search_url\": \"https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms}\"}]\n\nIf any of the search URLs in the list do not begin with \"https\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows a list of list of up to 10 search engines to be configured, one of which must be marked as the default search engine. The encoding does not need to be specified. Starting in Microsoft Edge 80, the suggest_url and image_search_url parameters are optional. The optional parameter, image_search_post_params (consists of comma-separated name/value pairs), is available starting in Microsoft Edge 80.\n\nStarting in Microsoft Edge 83, search engine discovery can be enabled with the allow_search_engine_discovery optional parameter. This parameter must be the first item in the list. If allow_search_engine_discovery is not specified, search engine discovery will be disabled by default. Starting in Microsoft Edge 84, this policy can be set as a recommended policy to allow search provider discovery. The allow_search_engine_discovery optional parameter does not need to be added.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users cannot add, remove, or change any search engine in the list. Users can set their default search engine to any search engine in the list.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or not configured, users can modify the search engines list as desired.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1320","uuid":"d11e4553-a235-4805-aec4-9f31ccf21173","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F47209B1C0B6592FC647BD09E7F6562EC6FD3B1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The default search provider must be set to use an encrypted connection.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235727","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235727","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235727","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235727r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235727","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000010","rule_title":"Data Synchronization must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Disable synchronization of data using Microsoft sync services\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Disable synchronization of data using Microsoft sync services\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SyncDisabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disables data synchronization in Microsoft Edge. This policy also prevents the sync consent prompt from appearing.\n\nIf this policy is not set or applied as recommended, users will be able to turn sync on or off. If this policy is applied as mandatory, users will not be able to turn on sync.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5900","uuid":"8b748827-14b7-4e6d-bac0-3b4f2d58cda9","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 194FC07DAA2170D2E09EAC64B5521C5D6AAC213A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Data Synchronization must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235728","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235728","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235728","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235728r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235728","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000011","rule_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable network prediction\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't predict network actions on any network connection\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable network prediction\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't predict network actions on any network connection\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for NetworkPredictionOptions is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables network prediction and prevents users from changing this setting.\n\nThis controls DNS prefetching, TCP and SSL pre-connection, and pre-rendering of web pages.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, network prediction is enabled but the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- NetworkPredictionAlways (0) = Predict network actions on any network connection.\n- NetworkPredictionWifiOnly (1) = Not supported; if this value is used it will be treated as if \"Predict network actions on any network connection\" (0) was set.\n- NetworkPredictionNever (2) = Do not predict network actions on any network connection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8821","uuid":"88e2197b-da6c-46e5-897f-faa1199832a0","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3463BB04B9E7EAA31B89E9DDBF219D4ECF8179A1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Network prediction must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235729","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235729","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235729","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235729r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235729","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000012","rule_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable search suggestions\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable search suggestions\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SearchSuggestEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables web search suggestions in the Microsoft Edge Address Bar and Auto-Suggest List, and prevents users from changing this policy.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, web search suggestions are used.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, web search suggestions are never used; however, local history and local favorites suggestions still appear. If this policy is disabled, neither the typed characters nor the URLs visited will be included in telemetry to Microsoft.\n\nIf this policy is not set, search suggestions are enabled but the user can change that.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6228","uuid":"98eecffd-f825-4186-a3d3-265ba7274d30","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA7C59B36B980671173EF22A594A1773C0C57C13\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Search suggestions must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235730","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235730","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235730","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235730r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235730","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000013","rule_title":"Importing of autofill form data must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of autofill form data\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of autofill form data\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportAutofillFormData\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import autofill form data from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to manually import autofill data is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, autofill form data is not imported at first run, and users cannot import it manually.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, autofill data is imported at first run, and users can choose whether to import this data manually during later browsing sessions.\n\nThis policy cannot be set as a recommendation. This means that Microsoft Edge will import autofill data on first run, but users can select or clear autofill data option during manual import.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1726","uuid":"e9bd4185-76e4-4e5a-8830-9905da4ba3a9","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E0048C4E8AD1E0209D658463E566C375361D51F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of autofill form data must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235731","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235731","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235731","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235731r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235731","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000014","rule_title":"Importing of browser settings must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browser settings\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browser settings\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportBrowserSettings\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import browser settings from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Browser settings check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, browser settings are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, browser settings are imported at first run, and users can choose whether to import them manually during later browsing sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8635","uuid":"42be9c1f-62df-4022-92c6-cf1f62971b06","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F2D1740DD482ECDA70812171609F767BF4A8D29\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of browser settings must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235732","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235732","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235732","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235732r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235732","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000015","rule_title":"Importing of cookies must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of cookies\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of cookies\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportCookies\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import cookies from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, cookies are not imported on first run.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, cookies are imported on first run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4784","uuid":"a8322096-2f1d-4e57-8bd8-c8c524526f35","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E272729098B8D4D43B8EA760950115887A237BB8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of cookies must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235733","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235733","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235733","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235733r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235733","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000016","rule_title":"Importing of extensions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of extensions\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of extensions\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportExtensions\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import extensions from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Extensions check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, extensions are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5842","uuid":"6420f6f6-c8b1-4bd5-8e08-938c0d5cfa6a","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2204BAAF725D3268E6AACE8E05CD7D6C6184D754\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of extensions must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235734","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235734","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235734","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-235734r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235734","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000017","rule_title":"Importing of browsing history must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browsing history\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browsing history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows users to import their browsing history from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Browsing history check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, browsing history data is not imported at first run, and users cannot import this data manually.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9052","uuid":"6710b265-7b9f-4f1b-91c4-4504dfaa51c3","stig_uuid":"95ebad44-34ec-409d-9843-560e8458e095","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 70DF396D301E48D020C50D9961A4391E2400586E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Importing of browsing history must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Microsoft Edge browser."},{"group_id_src":"V-235735","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235735","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235735","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_